# _headers — Cloudflare Pages custom headers
#
# Previously had a Content-Encoding: br rule for /index.wasm — that's
# gone now that build.py splits large wasm files into .part1/.part2
# instead of brotli-compressing them (see setup/build.py, section 5
# of the README). Those parts are raw bytes, not brotli, so keeping
# `Content-Encoding: br` here would make browsers try to brotli-decode
# them and fail.
#
# Left empty for now — add rules back here if/when we need custom
# caching or headers again (e.g. Cache-Control for .part1/.part2 or
# wasm-loader.js). Whatever goes here gets copied into export/ as-is
# by build.py on every run — this file (in game/template/) is the
# source of truth, don't edit the copy inside export/ directly.
